				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Too much aggro...<a name="59594"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 30 04 11:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This is just sort of a &quot;heads-up&quot; post.
<br />

<br />
Background:
<br />
1.  Weapon Affinity 5
<br />
2.  Nearly maxxed DEX with Shaman buffs
<br />
3.  Spell Casting Fury 3
<br />
3.  Dedgerex's Flintforged Cudgel
<br />

<br />
I've recently noticed something while doing some pickup LDoN groups.  I seem to be gaining too much aggro in melee.  I hadn't noticed it until I got the cudgel.   It hasn't really been a serious problem yet, but I think some MTs and some Healers have gotten at least slightly annoyed about it.
<br />

<br />
It seems like (to me) that the 600(ish) point procs (and the occasional 1200(ish) proc) is pulling more aggro than would be normal for just being simple damage accumulation.
<br />

<br />
*Shrug*  Maybe this is normal and I'm just not used to the increased aggro-element of it yet.
<br />

<br />
I will say this, though, aggro problems aside, the procs are SWEET on this weapon!  Even with the crappy physical dmg/dly ratio, this weapon's proc is NICE!  I don't notice it getting resisted very much at all on blue-cons.  Hardly ever, actually.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">-treeb<br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308563">(Tree)ble Clef</a><br>-------<br>"Music should strike fire from the heart of man, and bring tears from the eyes of woman."  -Ludwig van Beethoven</span></td>
