				<td colspan="2"><span>I use the cudgel as well, but it still is not enough to pull a mob off a guildies ranger if we are both beating the crap out of it.  Once in awhile I would get a few swings after a 1250 critical, but overall maybe 10% tanked vs his 90%....and sometimes I would get the kill<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  5 dots switching out instruments and mele..even then I needed a lot of procs to get the kill.
<br />

<br />
Cudgel definitely seems to outdamage many high ratio non-proc weapons if you have all the aa to max your proc damage.  
<br />

<br />
Makes me wonder if the best weapons in the game are really the best for a bard.  I would hope that any bard only weapon in the expansion would have a big honking proc, because a far inferrior ratio weapon with a proc might just turn out to be the best there is for a Bard.  If we can't mele...bring on the proc.
<br />

<br />
Moose</span></td>
