			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Too much aggro...<a name="68381"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 28 04 1:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I have a 65 Bst, decked out pretty nice for a non-uber guild. I have the Cudgel in his primary with WA2, and Velium Inlaid Claws in Sec. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Never compare aggro on weapons from another class to a bard.  Why do I say this? I could stick a SEM mainhand (with a rune/stun, which is supposed to be considerable aggro by itself), pair it with something else with two stuns, and still get aggro stolen from me by a level 56 necromancer casting snare and one poison dot, while I twist four chants. A rune and three stuns would be enough for any other class, but is obviously not enough for a bard.
<br />

<br />
The sole exception to this, that I have seen, is the BoC. I presume this is because hate from spells is generated in two forms: raw +hate, which exists as the effect itself (as in the case of the BoC), and secondary hate caused by what the effect does (for instance, how much hate a resist debuff or snare or mez will provide). I assume bards have some global hate reduction on the latter, which is why we generate almost no hate even if we hos/slow/mez the mob on inc (at least I know I don't, warriors can still peel from me with an arrow and proximity). 
<br />

<br />
Personally this is a good thing anyway, I don't want full hate calculations when I'm twisting three songs on a group and AE mana in a 50 person raid. Of course, it makes aggro control somewhat more difficult, and weapons like the BoC extremely valuable for bards.
<br />

<br />
On a side note, are there any other bard usable weapons with pure +hate? What are these 'remains of sythax,' I've never heard them mentioned before?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
